For 90 years, Social Security has been a lifeline for America’s seniors.

We’re fighting to keep it that way.

I’ll always fight to protect Social Security.

That means ending the tax on benefits and providing real relief— like helping seniors with property taxes—  without touching a penny of your earned benefits.

We need to:
✔ Protect benefits
✔ Improve service
✔ Cut taxes for seniors

And we can do it by making the wealthiest Americans pay what they owe.

Let’s be clear: Social Security is your money. You’ve earned it.

You deserve your full benefits AND excellent service.

Why make it harder to get help?

They’re hoping frustration will build…so they can privatize Social Security.

Here’s the truth:
❌ It’s not permanent.
❌ It’s only for some working seniors.
❌ Most seniors get little or nothing.

AND everyone is still paying taxes on their benefits.

They even sent an email to 90+ million seniors claiming their big bill “eliminated taxes on Social Security benefits.”

That’s false.

But our work is far from over.

The Trump Administration is firing staff and closing Social Security offices across the country— making it harder for people to get help.

We used a rare tool in Congress— a discharge petition— to force a vote. It worked. 

The bill passed the House and then the Senate on the final day of the 118th Congress.

Now millions of public retirees are getting the benefits they’ve earned. https://t.co/JcZezOvz8r

That’s why, late last year, we helped lead the charge to pass the Social Security Fairness Act.

For decades, two provisions unfairly penalized public retirees— teachers, nurses, police officers— who paid into BOTH a public pension and Social Security.

Today marks 90 years since President Roosevelt signed Social Security into law.

It’s one of the most successful programs in American history— lifting millions out of poverty and giving seniors the dignity they’ve earned. 🧵👇🏼 https://t.co/qFv2keyavp
